{{Quote|Vote for Palpatine. Vote for the Empire. Make Mon Mothma vote for him too. Be good little Senators. Mind your manners and keep your heads down. And keep doing all those things we can't talk about. All those things I can't know. Promise me, Bail.|[[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] during the [[Declaration of a New Order]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith (novelization)">[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' novelization]]</ref>}}
The '''Delegation of 2000''' was the group of [[Senator/Legends|senators]], many of whom were part of the [[Loyalist Committee/Legends|Loyalist Committee]], who created and presented the [[Petition of 2000]] to [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] near the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The delegation were concerned about the Chancellor's continued usage of emergency powers even as the Clone Wars were nearing its conclusion&mdash;especially the formation of the position of [[Moff/Legends|Moff]]. Many of the senators feared for the future of [[Democracy/Legends|democracy]] in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="Incognito">{{InsiderCite|143|Incognito}}</ref> 

After the [[Declaration of a New Order|formation]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], the new [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] [[Senatorial arrests/Legends|arrested]]<ref name="meena">{{DB|character|meenatills|Tills, Meena}}</ref> at least sixty-three senators, although some were merely detained temporarily, perhaps as a warning from the new [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]].<ref name="Millennium Falcon">[[Millennium Falcon (novel)|''Millennium Falcon'']]</ref>

Following the [[Battle of Kashyyyk (19 BBY)|Battle of Kashyyyk]], half the Delegation of 2000 withdrew their signatures from the petition. However, many of them still quietly opposed Palpatine's [[Imperial Era/Legends|rule]], and it was they who, in the wake of the [[Ghorman Massacre/Legends|Ghorman Massacre]], eventually formed the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].

==Behind the scenes==
*While ''[[Republic HoloNet News Special Inaugural Edition 16:5:241]]'' and ''[[Dark Lord: The Rise of Darth Vader]]'' state that Bail Organa was a member of the Delegation, the [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|Episode III novelization]] maintains that he was not.
*The subplot involving the Delegation of 2000 was cut from the film but is featured on the Revenge of the Sith DVD and novelization.

